President Donald Trump has issued a message urging America's state and local leaders to support the men and women of U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP). He commended their efforts in enforcing the legal immigration system and protecting national security. The President called for public expressions of support for ICE and CBP, as well as voluntary compliance with federal law and cooperation with these organizations in removing dangerous criminal aliens from communities. He condemned the "Abolish ICE" movement and highlighted the important role of ICE and CBP in preventing terrorism. The President emphasized the need for a functioning legal immigration system and urged state and local leaders to work together towards this goal.